<section id="about" class="about">
  <hr class="hairline" />
  <div class="about-inner">

    <p class="mono file-marker">05 / ABOUT</p>

    <h2 class="heading">Anton.</h2>

    <!-- ===== THREE-ACT ORIGIN STORY ===== -->
    <div class="story">

      <div class="act" data-act="1">
        <p class="act-marker mono">ACT I / ORIGIN</p>
        <div class="act-body">
          <p>
            I grew up inside the operating room of family businesses involved in
            over $40 million of exits. Business sales. Land sales. The slow,
            deliberate construction of wealth, observed from a kitchen table that
            doubled as a strategy room. I learned how money is actually made
            before I learned how it was supposed to be made.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="act" data-act="2">
        <p class="act-marker mono">ACT II / SCALE</p>
        <div class="act-body">
          <p>
            At a privately-held Australian company that started under $10M annual
            revenue, I led the operational work that scaled it past $200M a year.
            The company can't be named publicly. The growth wasn't an accident.
            It was a sequence of correctly identified leaks, plugged in the right
            order.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="act" data-act="3">
        <p class="act-marker mono">ACT III / THE INSIGHT</p>
        <div class="act-body">
          <p>
            What I see in small Australian businesses now is the same pattern,
            inverted. Twenty, thirty, forty years of trading. Product-market fit
            proven by the fact that the business still exists. And yet nobody has
            ever sat down and asked where the revenue is leaking. There are six-
            figure opportunities sitting in plain view, on every street, in every
            strip mall. Nobody is harvesting them.
          </p>
          <p class="arc-resolution">That is what INKZ is for.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div><!-- /story -->

    <!-- ===== EXHIBITS BLOCK ===== -->
    <div class="exhibits-divider">
      <hr class="hairline" />
      <p class="mono divider-label">// EXHIBITS</p>
    </div>

    <p class="framing-line">
      These aren't claims about growth delivered for you. They're proof of proximity to the levers.
    </p>

    <div class="exhibits">

      <div class="exhibit" data-exhibit="A">
        <p class="exhibit-index mono">EXHIBIT A</p>
        <h3 class="exhibit-title">Meta APAC.</h3>
        <p class="exhibit-body">
          Direct line to AU / ASIA 2IC at Meta. Singapore office visit. Summit invitations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="exhibit" data-exhibit="B">
        <p class="exhibit-index mono">EXHIBIT B</p>
        <h3 class="exhibit-title">TikTok Australia.</h3>
        <p class="exhibit-body">
          Founding beta tester. Scoped previously-restricted policy use cases. Helped convince
          board to allow a whitelist program (which subsequently extended to invite-only then
          application-based).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!--
        FUTURE EXHIBITS: Add additional exhibit blocks here following the pattern below.
        Copy the template, increment the letter, and fill in title + body copy.

        <div class="exhibit" data-exhibit="C">
          <p class="exhibit-index mono">EXHIBIT C</p>
          <h3 class="exhibit-title">Title here.</h3>
          <p class="exhibit-body">
            Body copy here. One to three lines. Factual, restrained.
          </p>
        </div>
      -->

      <!-- Placeholder element for future exhibits. Hidden from display, preserves DOM pattern. -->
      <div class="exhibit" data-exhibit-placeholder aria-hidden="true" hidden></div>

    </div><!-- /exhibits -->

  </div><!-- /about-inner -->
</section>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: var(--space-24) var(--space-8);
  }

  .about > .hairline {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-24);
  }

  .about-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-body-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ---- File marker ---- */
  .file-marker {
    color: var(--graphite-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* ---- Section heading ---- */
  .heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--type-600);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* ===== THREE-ACT STORY ===== */

  .story {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .act {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
  }

  .act:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  .act-marker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--type-100);
    font-weight: var(--weight-medium);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--graphite-soft);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .act-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-300);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--graphite);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .act-body p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  /* Arc resolution: the final line of the story. Set apart, in ink, slightly larger.
     Not a marketing punchline. Just the end of the argument. */
  .arc-resolution {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-500);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  /* ===== EXHIBITS ===== */

  .exhibits-divider {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .exhibits-divider .hairline {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .divider-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--type-100);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--graphite-soft);
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* Framing line: restrained italic, slightly larger than body. Not a headline. */
  .framing-line {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-400);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--graphite);
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  /* Exhibits: document evidence blocks. Numbered, hairline-separated. No chrome. */
  .exhibits {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .exhibit {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .exhibit:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  /* Hide the placeholder div from the border logic */
  .exhibit[data-exhibit-placeholder] {
    display: none;
  }

  .exhibit-index {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--type-100);
    font-weight: var(--weight-medium);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--graphite-soft);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .exhibit-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    font-size: var(--type-400);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .exhibit-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-300);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--graphite);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  /* ===== RESPONSIVE ===== */

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .about {
      padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-6);
    }

    .about > .hairline {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
    }

    .heading {
      font-size: var(--type-500);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    }

    .story {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    }

    .arc-resolution {
      font-size: var(--type-400);
    }

    .framing-line {
      font-size: var(--type-300);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    }
  }
</style>
